  "prompt": "What website theme is www.Mould-solutions.com using?",
  "response": "As of my last update, I can't directly analyze or view live websites, including www.mould-solutions.com. However, you can determine the website theme by inspecting the site yourself. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. **Visit the Website**: Go to [www.mould-solutions.com](http://www.mould-solutions.com) in your browser.\n  \n2. **Inspect the Page**: Right-click anywhere on the page and select \"Inspect\" or \"Inspect Element\" from the context menu. This will open the browser's developer tools.\n\n3. **Look for Theme Information**: In the developer tools, you can search through the HTML or CSS files for clues about the theme. Common places to look include:\n   - The `<head>` section of the HTML for links to stylesheets or meta tags that might mention the theme.\n   - The CSS files themselves might include comments at the top indicating the theme name or framework being used.\n\n4. **Use Online Tools**: There are online tools and services that can analyze a website and provide details about its theme, plugins, and other technologies it uses. Examples include [BuiltWith](https://builtwith.com/) or [Wappalyzer](https://www.wappalyzer.com/). Simply enter the website URL into one of these tools to get detailed information.\n\n5. **Check the Footer**: Sometimes, themes credit their creators in the footer of the website. Scroll down to the bottom of the page and see if there\u2019s any mention of the theme name or developer.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to determine what theme www.mould-solutions.com is using. If you're unable to find the information, it might be a custom theme developed specifically for the site.",
